ZH: 1. 他的祖母得了痴呆症。
EN: 1. His grandmother has dementia.
ZH: 2. 这个病人的病情越来越严重，已经开始出现痴呆的症状了。
EN: 2. The condition of this patient is getting worse, and dementia symptoms have started to appear.
ZH: 3. 这家养老院专门为痴呆患者提供照料。
EN: 3. This nursing home specializes in caring for dementia patients.
ZH: 4. 痴呆症是一种智力退化的疾病。
EN: 4. Dementia is a disease that causes intellectual decline.
ZH: 5. 我的爷爷很健忘，恐怕有点痴呆了。
EN: 5. My grandfather is very forgetful; he might have a touch of dementia.
ZH: 6. 这本书是关于痴呆症的最新研究。
EN: 6. This book is about the latest research on dementia.
ZH: 7. 这位医生正在研究如何延缓痴呆症的进展。
EN: 7. This doctor is researching ways to slow down the progression of dementia.
ZH: 8. 痴呆症患者需要特殊的护理和关爱。
EN: 8. Dementia patients require special care and attention.
ZH: 9. 痴呆并不仅仅影响老年人。
EN: 9. Dementia doesn't only affect older adults.
ZH: 10. 她开始说一些不合理的事情，这让我们怀疑她是否正在发展痴呆症。
EN: 10. She has started saying some unreasonable things, which made us wonder if she is developing dementia.
ZH: 11. 痴呆患者的记忆力逐渐衰退。
EN: 11. The memory of dementia patients declines gradually.
ZH: 12. 这种药物可以缓解痴呆症状。
EN: 12. This medication can alleviate dementia symptoms.
ZH: 13. 我们尽力提供一个安全和舒适的环境给痴呆症患者。
EN: 13. We strive to provide a safe and comfortable environment for dementia patients.
ZH: 14. 她通过健脑游戏来预防痴呆症。
EN: 14. She prevents dementia by playing brain-training games.
ZH: 15. 这位科学家正在寻找解决痴呆症之谜的答案。
EN: 15. This scientist is searching for answers to the mystery of dementia.
ZH: 16. 痴呆症带来的认知障碍会使日常生活变得困难。
EN: 16. Cognitive impairments caused by dementia make daily life challenging.
ZH: 17. 他被确诊为早期痴呆症，但他仍然可以独立生活。
EN: 17. He has been diagnosed with early-stage dementia, but he can still live independently.
ZH: 18. 高龄是患痴呆症的主要风险因素之一。
EN: 18. Advanced age is one of the main risk factors for developing dementia.
ZH: 19. 这部纪录片讲述了一位痴呆症患者和她的家人的故事。
EN: 19. This documentary tells the story of a dementia patient and her family.
ZH: 20. 这个项目旨在提高人们对痴呆症的认识和理解。
EN: 20. This project aims to raise awareness and understanding of dementia among people.
